[[File:Star_Wars_RPG_Padded_Flight_Suit.jpg|thumb|A padded flight suit]]
The '''padded flight suit''' was a type of [[Armor/Legends|armor]] favored by [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighter]] [[Pilot/Legends|pilots]] all over [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]]. The one-piece flight suit protected the wearer from a variety of conditions including decompression, g-forces, and harmful environments. Though not specifically designed for it, the armor was protective in combat to a limited degree. These suits came standard with a matching helmet and gloves that would complete an airtight seal, allowing the wearer to survive for up to 10 hours in a hostile environment. The padded flight suit typically cost 800 [[Galactic Credit Standard/Legends|credits]] and weighed roughly 5 kg.

==Behind the scenes==
This armor is identical to the "[[battle armor]]" armor seen in both ''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic]]'' games.

